# Kris Tong Portfolio — Working Context

A static personal portfolio / case-study website for **Kris (Lingwei) Tong**, a
Digital Experience Designer & UX Researcher. Deployed as a GitHub Pages site
(`kristong.github.io`). There is **no build step, framework, or package manager** —
just hand-authored HTML with Tailwind loaded from a CDN, plus a couple of small
vanilla-JS enhancements.

## Tech stack

- **HTML** (one file per page, no templating/includes).
- **Tailwind CSS** via CDN: `<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>`.
- **Dark mode** is enabled per page with `tailwind.config = { darkMode: 'media' }`
  (follows the OS `prefers-color-scheme`; there is no manual toggle).
- **Vanilla JS only** — no bundler, no dependencies. Two reusable behaviors:
  - `assets/lightbox.js` — click-to-zoom lightbox; auto-attaches to every
    `<img>` inside an `<article>` on project detail pages.
  - Inline scripts for the sticky-sidebar "spring" animation and scroll
    restoration (see below).

## Page map

| File | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `index.html` | Home / about page: bio, skills grid, work experience. |
| `work.html` | "Selected Projects" list; each card links to a detail page. |
| `project-*.html` | One detail page per project (case study). |
| `assets/` | Images, project media, and `lightbox.js`. |
| `README.md` | One-line description only. |

### Projects (8 detail pages)

`tourism`, `tourmaster`, `sia`, `mataliki`, `wananga`, `cvr`, `c4`, `napos`.
Each has a `project-<slug>.html` page, a card thumbnail at
`assets/project-<slug>.jpg`, and (most have) a media folder at
`assets/Project-detial-materials/<slug>/`.

## Shared layout conventions (keep these consistent across pages)

- **Body classes:**
  `bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 font-sans antialiased`.
- **Sticky top nav:** identical markup on every page — a `sticky top-0 z-50`
  wrapper containing a `max-w-6xl` nav with `Home` (`index.html`) and `Work`
  (`work.html`) links. The active link gets
  `text-gray-900 dark:text-white border-b-2 border-gray-900 dark:border-white pb-1`.
- **Sidebar / two-column layout** (`index.html`, `work.html`):
  `max-w-6xl` main with a `md:w-1/4` `<aside>` (avatar + contact links) and a
  `md:w-3/4` content `<section>`. The aside uses `md:sticky md:top-28` and
  `id="sidebar-spring"`.
- **Detail pages** (`project-*.html`): narrower `max-w-4xl` main, a "← Back to
  List" link to `work.html`, a `21/9` hero `<figure>`, a metadata `<header>`
  (Role/Type, Platform, Timeline, plus Funding/Location/etc.), and an
  `<article class="prose ...">` body that mixes paragraphs with image grids
  (`grid-cols-2`/`grid-cols-3`). Detail pages load `assets/lightbox.js` at the
  end of `<body>`.
- **Images** use `onerror` fallbacks to `via.placeholder.com` so missing assets
  degrade gracefully.
- **"See Details"** buttons are pill-shaped dark/white buttons; optional
  external "Learn more ↗" links sit beside them.

### Scroll-restoration behavior (work.html ⇄ detail pages)

`work.html` saves `window.scrollY` to `sessionStorage` (`workScrollY`) when a
`project-*` link is clicked, hides the page (`opacity:0`) on return, restores the
saved position on `load`, then fades back in. Preserve this when editing
`work.html` navigation so returning from a detail page does not jump.

### Sidebar "spring" animation

An inline IIFE on `index.html` / `work.html` nudges `#sidebar-spring` slightly on
scroll then springs it back with a cubic-bezier transition. It is purely
decorative.

## Conventions for adding/editing content

- To **add a project**: create `project-<slug>.html` from an existing detail page
  as a template, add a card to `work.html`, add `assets/project-<slug>.jpg`, and
  (optionally) a media folder. Keep the nav, body classes, and dark-mode config
  identical to existing pages.
- Match the existing Tailwind utility patterns rather than introducing custom CSS.
- Keep all `dark:` variants in sync whenever you touch colored elements.
- Content tone is first-person, outcome-oriented case-study writing.

## Known issues / cleanup opportunities (verify before "fixing" — may be intentional)

- **Naming inconsistency for the Matariki project.** The file/asset slug is
  `mataliki` and the `work.html` card title reads **"Mataliki Hana Nui"**, but
  the detail page (`project-mataliki.html`) title is **"Matariki Hunga Nui"**.
  "Matariki Hunga Nui" appears to be the correct te reo Māori spelling.
- **Misspelled asset folder**: `assets/Project-detial-materials/`
  ("detial" → "detail"). Renaming would require updating every `src` reference
  across the `project-*.html` pages.
- **Stray temp file**: `assets/Project-detial-materials/~$oject Detailed Pages.docx`
  is a leftover Microsoft Office lock/temp file and can be removed.
- **Source `.docx`** `assets/Project-detial-materials/Project Detailed Pages.docx`
  holds the source copy for the detail pages.
- **Placeholder GitHub link** in `index.html` sidebar (`href="#"`).
- Repeated inline `<script>` blocks (sidebar spring) are duplicated across pages
  rather than shared from `assets/`; could be extracted like `lightbox.js`.

## Testing / preview

No automated tests or CI. To preview locally, serve the folder statically, e.g.:

```bash
python3 -m http.server 8000
```

then open `http://localhost:8000/index.html`. Tailwind and the placeholder image
fallbacks require network access.
